  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food Security Program with LeSea Global Feed the Hungry - Uganda - 2016</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Stop Hunger now provides this program with 10 containers of food assistance</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">These meals will be distributed through LeSEA Global: Feed the Hungry&apos;s daily feeding program for impoverished children in seven schools throughout the greater Kampala area of Uganda. After Stop Hunger Now meals first started distributing meals in January 2011, enrollment soared from 650 to 2,014 children by the end of the year. Now LeSEA Global: Feed the Hungry reaches more than 15,000 children every day. Right now, the program in Uganda faces even greater needs as refugees from fighting in the Democratic Republic of the Congo make their way to Uganda. Feed the Hungry has committed to providing food and other basic needs--including clean water--to refugees in the Rwamwanja and Kiryandongo camps in Western Uganda.</narrative>
  </description>
